ates; we’ll use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiftCrossUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" template. The ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiftCrossUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" template uses ","type":"text"},{"code":"DefaultBackend","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to select the most appropriate backend at compile time.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh","code":["swift bundler create HelloWorld --template SwiftCrossUI","cd HelloWorld"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Running your app","anchor":"Running-your-app"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Running your new app with Swift Bundler is as simple as it gets!"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh","code":["swift bundler run"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On macOS you can provide the ","type":"text"},{"code":"--device <device_name_or_id>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" option to run the app on a connacted iOS or tvOS device, or the ","type":"text"},{"code":"--simulator <simulator_name_or_id>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" option to run the app in a simulator.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh","code":["# You can use any substring of the target device name. For example,","# \"iPhone\" matches any device connected with \"iPhone\" in its name.","swift bundler run --device \"iPhone\"","swift bundler run --simulator \"iPhone 15\""]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Making a change","anchor":"Making-a-change"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Open ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sources\/HelloWorld\/HelloWorldApp.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in an editor of your choosing. Change ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"Hello, World!\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"Hello, Earth!\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Repeat the previous step to verify that your changes get reflected.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"All done","anchor":"All-done"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":